THE Road Traffic Management Corporation has come up with a strategy to reduce road deaths. Traffic law enforcement officers will use road safety awareness campaigns to send the word out there.The National Road Traffic Safety Strategy will try to reduce the number of crashes and deaths by 50%.In emphasising safety, the Road Traffic Management Corporation has offered the following tips to motorists and road users:You must avoid alcohol and heavy foods if you are driving for long distances;Rest every two hours of driving;Don&rsquo;t pressure your visitors when it&rsquo;s time to leave, and don&rsquo;t let your friends walk home drunk; If you&rsquo;re taking any medication, make sure it does not affect your driving and make you drowsy; and If you are new to driving, take someone with you on your trip who has more driving experience.